The paper focuses on a mobile robot's perception of obstacles using a camera and a proximity sensor, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves training a convolutional neural network on automatically-acquired datasets, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the usage of the approach as the sole input of an obstacle-avoidance controller, which involves control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
